# Write a program that prompts the user to enter a three-digit integer and determines whether it is a palindrome number. 
#A number is a palindrome if it reads the same from right to left and from left to right

num = input("Enter a three-digit integer: ")

if num == num[::-1]:
    print(f"{num} is a palindrome number.")
else:
    print(f"{num} is not a palindrome number.")
